cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for human pose estimation in videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel ConvNet architecture, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of optical flow and the alignment of heatmap predictions from neighbouring frames could be relevant to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with video processing, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of a graphical model could be relevant to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics and Control).
